One person was allegedly killed by suspected herdsmen who stormed Oha village in the Imeko-Afon Local Government Area of Ogun State. Sources said the attack was carried out around 1 a.m on Sunday. The Nation gathered that the herdsmen also destroyed buildings and farmlands in the community. The victim identified as Dele Olowoniyi was hacked to death by the herders while he was fleeing the village. It was said that the hoodlums who were armed with guns left for Iwoye-Ketu after carrying out the attack.